option.helptext:
When enabled, the bad word filter will include entries with the tag "test" allowing for the testing of the filter's application without the need to fill objects with genuinely offensive content.

The current test entry is:

Match: xkc*d {{K|// the c may be repeated an unlimited number of times}}
Severity: 3 (strong)
Exceptions:
 vxkc*d {{K|// the starting v results in no match}}
 xkc*dv {{K|// the ending v results in no match}}
 yxkc*dy {{K|// surrounded by y results in no match, but should match without one or the other }}

The default is {{w|Disabled}}.

Sets the chance when visiting a zone that an eligible bones file will be searched for and, if found, loaded into a zone.

{{c|}} almost never - {{C|0.1%}}
{{c|}} rarely - {{C|0.5%}}
{{c|}} uncommon - {{C|1.25%}}
{{c|}} default - {{C|2.0%}}
{{c|}} sometimes - {{C|5.0%}}
{{c|}} frequently - {{C|10.0%}}
{{c|}} often - {{C|20.0%}}
{{c|}} not quite half - {{C|40.0%}}
{{c|}} custom - enables a button to enter a {{C|custom value}}

Keep in mind, humans are notoriously bad at judging probability.

Note: if you would like to disable encountering bones altogether, there is a debug option (in the {{c|Debug}} category) to pause bones encounters.

The default is {{W|2.0%}}.

Sets the {{c|dis}}{{C|advantage}} amount when rolling for a character's level during Bones Mode character generation.

"Low" rolls with disadvantage, that is: it rolls multiple times and takes the lowest result.
"High" rolls with advantage, as above, but taking the highest result.

Bones Mode characters are always between level 5 and level 80 inclusive.

{{c|}} {{Y|extremely low}}  - 4x {{c|dis}}{{C|advantage}}, average {{rules|17.2}}, 50% of rolls {{K|under}} {{rules|15}}
{{c|}} {{Y|very low}}       - 3x {{c|dis}}{{C|advantage}}, average {{rules|19.7}}, 50% of rolls {{K|under}} {{rules|17}}
{{c|}} {{M|low}}            - 2x {{c|dis}}{{C|advantage}}, average {{rules|23.5}}, 50% of rolls {{K|under}} {{rules|21}}
{{c|}} {{Y|slightly low}}   - 1x {{c|dis}}{{C|advantage}}, average {{rules|29.8}}, 50% of rolls {{K|under}} {{rules|28}}
{{c|}} {{Y|even}}           - 0x {{c|dis}}/{{C|advantage}}, average {{rules|42.5}}, {{rules|even distribution}}
{{c|}} {{Y|slightly high}}  - 1x {{C|advantage}}, average {{rules|55.2}}, 50% of rolls {{Y|over}} {{rules|57}}
{{c|}} {{Y|high}}           - 2x {{C|advantage}}, average {{rules|61.5}}, 50% of rolls {{Y|over}} {{rules|64}}
{{c|}} {{Y|very high}}      - 3x {{C|advantage}}, average {{rules|65.3}}, 50% of rolls {{Y|over}} {{rules|68}}
{{c|}} {{Y|extremely high}} - 4x {{C|advantage}}, average {{rules|67.8}}, 50% of rolls {{Y|over}} {{rules|70}}

The default is {{M|low}}.
